null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T18:57:28+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Jontay Porter #34 of the Toronto Raptors grabs a rebound during the game against the Detroit Pistons on March 13, 2024 at Little Caesars Arena in Detroit, Michigan.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XwxLf74Sg9g-zE_I1vVjmTnKKT4=/0x0:4309x2873/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285763/2079441973.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Brian Sevald / NBAE via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Di0D1R\">The NBA has permanently banned Toronto Raptors forward Jontay Porter from the league for violating its gambling rules, the league <a href=\"https://www.nba.com/news/jontay-porter-banned-from-nba\">said in a statement</a> on Wednesday. According to an internal investigation conducted by the NBA, Porter bet on NBA games, disclosed confidential information to other gamblers, and adjusted his participation in certain games to influence the outcome of certain bets.</p>\n<p id=\"MdJapR\">The league started looking into Porter after a March ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24133279/nba-bans-jontay-porter-sports-betting-gambling", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "NBA bans player for life over online sports betting", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T18:13:33+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Google Pixel 7A in coral on a wooden table showing rear panel.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-MjtiZER7e1HDPyMVszl5Hz-H0w=/0x0:2000x1333/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285641/DSC04630_processed.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Pixel 7A is a standout midrange smartphone that nearly performs like a flagship, now for an entry-level price.</em> | Photo by Allison Johnson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"WrTCh2\"></p>\n<p id=\"lLYO7p\"></p>\n<p id=\"EykOIl\">Google is expected to introduce the new <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/12/24128507/google-pixel-8a-colors-leak\">Pixel 8A</a> at its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/14/24101171/google-io-2024-announced-may-14-android-ai-gemini\">I/O developer conference</a> next month. That\u2019s probably a contributing factor for the new all-time low price we\u2019re seeing on the midrange <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23716677/google-pixel-7a-review-screen-camera-battery", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24133040/google-pixel-7a-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Pixel 7A is a knockout at its record-low $349", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T17:39:30+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The new, all-electric Atlas robot from Boston Dynamics, standing in a room with an illuminated face.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hrLc8YgPt96gnMI6vcIQ-O8uwLg=/0x29:1440x989/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285558/atlas_yellow.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Boston Dynamics.</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"PRtpQZ\">It\u2019s alive! A day after announcing it was <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24132451/boston-dynamics-atlas-robot-retirement\">retiring Atlas, its hydraulic robot</a>, Boston Dynamics has introduced <a href=\"https://bostondynamics.com/blog/electric-new-era-for-atlas/\">a new, all-electric version</a> of its humanoid machine. The next-generation Atlas robot is designed to offer a far greater range of movement than its predecessor. </p>\n<p id=\"EA0Vo9\">Boston Dynamics wanted the new version to show that Atlas can keep a humanoid form without limiting \u201chow a bipedal robot can move.\u201d The new version has been redesigned ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24133145/boston-dynamics-resurrects-atlas-humanoid-robot-electric-new", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Boston Dynamics\u2019 new Atlas robot is a swiveling, shape-shifting nightmare", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T17:27:26+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An astronaut in a spacesuit floating in the cockpit of her ship.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TfSQxI5GQHhgVzkXyBUSZUo84Ag=/482x0:3359x1918/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285520/For_All_Mankind_Photo_040105.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Tyner Rushing as Samantha Massey in </em>For All Mankind<em>.</em> | Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Z5NnhL\">Folks hoping to see more of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24002720/best-apple-tv-plus-shows-2023\">Apple TV Plus\u2019 <em>For All Mankind</em></a><em> </em>series are in for a treat, but the streamer is working on more than just a new season.</p>\n<p id=\"GpuBx1\">Today, <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/tv-pr/news/2024/04/apple-renews-globally-acclaimed-hit-space-drama-for-all-mankind-for-season-five-and-announces-new-spinoff-series-star-city/\">Apple announced</a> that <em>For All Mankind </em>has been renewed for a fifth season that will continue to chronicle the alternate ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24133154/for-all-mankind-season-five-star-city-spinoff", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple TV Plus\u2019 For All Mankind is getting a fifth season and a new spinoff series", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T17:01:16+00:00", "description": "<p>OnePlus could be a strong alternative to Google or Samsung for Wear OS smartwatches.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24132998/one-plus-watch-2-review-smartwatches-wearables\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24132998/one-plus-watch-2-review-smartwatches-wearables", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The OnePlus Watch 2 is what redemption looks like", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T16:58:24+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A close-up image of Samsung\u2019s 2022 Frame TV hanging on a wall with a bunch of cacti on display.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XePqD-y8CoA4t8vamUCUYqaq2TE=/38x0:1382x896/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285419/Samsung_Frame_2021.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Like most people, I\u2019d prefer to stare at a bunch of cacti in my living room rather than an uninspired black rectangle.</em> | Image: Samsung</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"BOEkkS\">Everyone may like watching movies on a big screen, but a hulking panel is nothing but an eyesore when turned off. That\u2019s why <strong>Samsung\u2019s Frame TV </strong>has become so popular over the last several years and why several TV manufacturers, including Amazon, have <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/9/28/23375992/amazon-fire-tv-omni-qled-specs-features-price\">begun to crib ideas</a> from the company\u2019s artsy panels. And while the Frame certainly isn\u2019t cheap, you can currently pick up the", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132220/samsung-frame-tv-jbl-flip-6-bluetooth-speaker-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Samsung\u2019s art-inspired Frame TVs are up to $1,000 off right now", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T16:47:14+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Artwork showing the Delta icon and the Apple App Store logo, with screenshots from the emulator.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1IEWAe4c4vAWwnzD832Y__n5iqA=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285354/delta_app_store.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Riley Testut</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"RprSG4\">The Delta emulator is <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/delta-game-emulator/id1048524688\">officially available on the Apple App Store</a> \u2014 for free \u2014 outside of the European Union, where it\u2019s available via the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24100979/altstore-europe-app-marketplace-price-games\">third-party AltStore PAL</a> app marketplace that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/e/23864505\">just went live</a>. </p>\n<p id=\"fEUzih\">The app marks the first significant and officially sanctioned game emulator for the iPhone since Apple <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/5/24122341/apple-app-store-game-emulat", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132984/delta-free-emulator-nintendo-gba-n64-iphone-app-store-us", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The free Delta game emulator for iPhones is live on Apple\u2019s App Store", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T16:38:58+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo showing people using Amazon\u2019s Just Walk Out technology in a sports store\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/WusIrBymMSrXqL34zImVx73aBoA=/103x0:1218x743/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285382/amazon_just_walk_out.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Amazon</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hqIBhp\">Amazon is pushing back on claims that its cashierless Just Walk Out technology is run by humans in India \u2014 not AI. In <a href=\"https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/retail/amazon-just-walk-out-dash-cart-grocery-shopping-checkout-stores\">a blog post on Wednesday</a>, the e-commerce giant calls these reports \u201cuntrue\u201d and says that a machine learning model powers its system.</p>\n<p id=\"UZkQrV\">Last week, <a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/amazons-just-walk-out-actually-1-000-people-in-india-2024-4\">reports started going around</a> that claimed Amazon employs around 1,000 workers in India to watch people shop and review purchases at st", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24133029/amazon-just-walk-out-cashierless-ai-india", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Amazon insists Just Walk Out isn\u2019t secretly run by workers watching you shop", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T16:30:16+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FsU4J3oAUlWhgcShsK7psjx95Hw=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285360/pal_promo.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>That \u20ac1.50 per year subscription does not include tax but does offset Apple\u2019s Core Technology Fee.</em> | Image: AltStore PAL</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"K0TqvT\">After <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24100979/altstore-europe-app-marketplace-price-games\">we recently tested it in beta</a>, the third-party iOS app store <a href=\"https://rileytestut.com/blog/2024/04/17/introducing-altstore-pal/\">AltStore PAL</a> is now live in the European Union thanks to Apple\u2019s compliance with the region\u2019s Digital Markets Act (DMA). The store requires a <a href=\"https://buy.stripe.com/6oEg2u80z5vI0Mg4gg\">\u20ac1.50 (plus tax)</a> annual subscription to cover Apple\u2019s Core Technology Fee (CTF) for installing the app marketplace itself. </p>\n<p id=\"Se4TTS\">Installing AltStore PAL requires c", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24100464/altstore-pal-dma-eu-launch-delta-nintendo-emulator-clip-clipboard-manager", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Third-party iPhone app store AltStore PAL is now live in Europe", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T16:00:33+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A still photo from the Netflix series Sweet Tooth.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PN6CpAwJonI5wMEkOG1Jqjvcyb0=/333x0:2784x1634/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285272/Sweet_Tooth_n_S3_E1_00_04_02_09R.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VPYJDX\">Gus and his friends are coming back to Netflix very soon. The streamer just announced that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22454611/sweet-tooth-netflix-post-apocalyptic-world-interview\">the post-apocalyptic series <em>Sweet Tooth</em></a> is returning on June 6th, and as part of the news, there\u2019s a first-look trailer at what this season has in store.</p>\n<p id=\"z0QcuR\">Based on the comic books by Jeff Lemire, <em>Sweet Tooth</em> is a different take on an end-of-the-world story. It takes place after a mysterious virus killed off much of humanity, while at the same time, new hybrid children \u2014 humans with animal features like antlers or pig noses \u2014", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24133003/sweet-tooth-season-3-netflix-trailer-release-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix\u2019s Sweet Tooth returns for season 3 in June", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Comcast Now logo on a laptop screen.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NT_Hl9NL6mR5Od3zq01U1K1yEis=/522x0:6147x3750/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285255/Laptop_Image_from_Verge.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Comcast</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"k9HiAO\">Comcast announced today that it\u2019s expanding its \u201cNow\u201d branding to include two prepaid services: Now Internet and Now Mobile. Of the two, the mobile plan appears to be genuinely new, as it\u2019s a prepaid cellular option that offers unlimited 5G data, talk, and text for $25 a month per line. The mobile plan also has free access to the company\u2019s Xfinity hotspots<em>.</em></p>\n<p id=\"bcOu9t\">That seems like a better deal than Xfinity\u2019s current prepaid mobile plans, which <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.xfinity.com%2Fmobile%2Flearn%2Fplan%2Fdetails&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F20", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132851/comcast-xfinity-now-mobile-prepaid-wireless", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Comcast rolls out \u2018Now\u2019 prepaid phone and internet plans", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A marketing image of Sony\u2019s Bravia 9 Mini LED TV.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OdClnhyrrTNuAYEkPNpqaW8Pyow=/0x10:1456x981/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285236/bravia9.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Sony</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"2eS1ZV\">At the premium end of home theater, Sony TVs are about as good as it gets \u2014 and have been for several years now. The company is lauded for its image processing and penchant for delivering fantastic picture quality in both its flagship sets and lower-cost options like the X90L. So there\u2019s pressure that comes with every refresh of the lineup. But Sony\u2019s not letting that stop it from taking some bold steps in 2024. </p>\n<p id=\"Jq98kw\">This year, the company\u2019s primary focus is on Mini LED. And more specifically, all eyes are on the top-of-the-line Bravia 9. There\u2019s still an OLED in the new roster \u2014 that\u2019s the Bravia 8 \u2014 and last year\u2019s A95K QD-OLED is also sticking around. But Sony ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132829/sony-2024-bravia-9-8-7-3-mini-led-oled-tv", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sony might have perfected Mini LED TVs with its new 2024 lineup", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T14:50:05+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of the shape of a brain on a circuitboard.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/AgI4OKQn8U6h5EAgH0UrptbGiLU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73285004/STK414_AI_CHATBOT_E.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos: Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ULkFg9\">The next generation of the text-to-image AI model Stable Diffusion is still in preview, but <a href=\"https://stability.ai/news/stable-diffusion-3-api\">Stability AI is making it available</a> to some developers via API and a new content creation platform. Stability AI says developers can now access Stable Diffusion 3 from its <a href=\"https://platform.stability.ai/docs/api-reference?_gl=1*1elp9gl*_ga*MTY1NDUzMTIwNC4xNzA3OTMwOTU4*_ga_W4CMY55YQZ*MTcxMzM2MjEzNy40LjEuMTcxMzM2MjU5Mi4wLjAuMA..#tag/Generate/paths/~1v2beta~1stable-image~1generate~1sd3/post\">Developer Platform</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"9MgnYM\">Stability AI s", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132927/stable-diffusion-3-api-availability-stability-ai", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Stability AI is giving more developers access to its next-gen text-to-image generator", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T13:35:11+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An artist conecpt of NASA\u2019s Dragonfly rotorcraft\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/M0cYPS6M8mo234Yhx40rdmjeaJg=/0x10:1920x1290/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73284759/NASA_Dragonfly.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>This artist mockup of Dragonfly soaring over Titan\u2019s dunes has... well, </em>Dune<em> vibes</em>. | Image: NASA / Johns Hopkins APL / Steve Gribben</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"rsmbsQ\">NASA has been given the go-ahead to send a flying drone-like lander to explore Titan, the largest of Saturn\u2019s 146 moons. </p>\n<p id=\"wjKnAb\">Targeting a July 2028 launch, the agency <a href=\"https://science.nasa.gov/missions/dragonfly/nasas-dragonfly-rotorcraft-mission-to-saturns-moon-titan-confirmed/\">announced on Tuesday</a> that it can now complete the final design for <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/27/18761441/nasa-new-frontiers-dragonfly-titan-saturn-moon-rotorcraft\">Dragonfly</a> \u2014 a Mars rover-sized rotorcraft that wi", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132824/nasa-dragonfly-mission-drone-saturn-moon-titan-greenlit", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "NASA has greenlit plans to send a giant drone to Saturn\u2019s largest moon", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T13:30:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Nintendo logo sits inside a black, red, and cream-colored design.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/G0l-576XkaKnpDdJMpi_blg_Rlw=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73284749/acastro_STK054_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>New year, new Nintendo indie showcase.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24132202/nintendo-indie-world-april-2024\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24132202/nintendo-indie-world-april-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "All the announcements from Nintendo\u2019s spring Indie World event", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T13:14:48+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of Sony\u2019s new PlayStation PC overlay.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/uWYynm83EALwaZ9RaRuRkgKNgfQ=/150x0:1772x1081/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73284702/4818432b5e653ea5ebe9ad51f9722bd1b6f4140b.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The new PlayStation PC overlay.</em> | Image: Sony</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"pblpsQ\">Sony is introducing a new PlayStation PC overlay and shared Trophies with its upcoming release of <em>Ghost of Tsushima Director\u2019s Cut</em> on May 16th. It\u2019s the first PlayStation game for PC that uses Sony\u2019s new PlayStation overlay, which, much like the Steam overlay, will provide access to a friend list, Trophies, Settings, and your PlayStation account.</p>\n<p id=\"ap1NKi\">\u201cThis feature is available on Windows PCs and will be accessible from the in-game menu or, for keyboard players, by pressing the \u201cSHIFT +F1\u201d shortcut on your keyboard,\u201d explains Julian Huijbregts, online community specialist at Nix", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132846/sony-playstation-pc-overlay-shared-trophies-ghost-of-tsushima", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sony\u2019s new PlayStation PC overlay and shared Trophies arrive with Ghost of Tsushima", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T13:05:31+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Elon Musk, in a tux, looking befuddled\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xZBBv6SH74BWpA2Ff3dYesrKCuY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73284696/STK171_L_Allen_Musk_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Lille Allen / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"JaeHrX\">Tesla is asking shareholders to vote for a second time on Elon Musk\u2019s massive compensation package, after <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/30/24056177/elon-musk-tesla-tornetta-55-billion-pay-package-rejected\">a Delaware judge voided the first one</a> earlier this year on the grounds that the approval process was \u201cdeeply flawed.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"9cTgvE\">Tesla shareholders <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/1/23/16922758/elon-musk-compensation-tesla\">approved the package in 2018</a>, which gave Musk incentive to hit specific milestones, including a market valuation of $650 billion, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/1/23/16922758/elon-musk-", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132827/tesla-elon-musk-pay-package-shareholder-vote-delaware", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Tesla is putting Elon Musk\u2019s pay package up for another vote after a judge voided the first one", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pw_98t_q2Jjmj2jSKas26nHeFpM=/0x0:3922x2615/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73284634/formlabs_form_4.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ZDMtWG\">Formlabs was <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2013/1/12/3867864/3d-printing-precisely-with-formlabs-and-the-form-1\">one of the early Kickstarter success stories</a>, and its laser-blasting 3D printers are now used by model makers, prototypers, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/9/24031738/formlabs-says-3d-printed-dentures-made-with-its-new-resin-look-like-the-real-thing\">dentists</a>, and maybe even <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/7/13/23207124/hasbro-formlabs-3d-print-figure-marvel-iron-man-spiderman\">action figure companies</a> around the globe. But its newest printers are ditching those resin-blasting lasers because they\u2019re comparatively slow.</p>\n<p id=\"VghZ1r\">With <a href=\"https://formlabs.com/3d-printers/form-4/\">the new Form 4</a>, Formlabs ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132558/formlabs-form-4-3d-printer-msla-resin", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Formlabs\u2019 new pro 3D printers claim 2\u20135x speed by ditching lasers for an LCD screen", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"EV charging station\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/EUZHGRGiivlPp_S5FxDGG4AorCs=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73284654/ahawkins_20210503_4551_0002.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Andrew J. Hawkins / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zLT197\">Google Maps is rolling out some new updates designed to make locating an electric vehicle charging station less stressful. And to accomplish this, it will (of course) lean heavily on artificial intelligence. </p>\n<p id=\"eLwl4W\">Google <a href=\"https://blog.google/products/maps/new-ways-to-power-up-your-electric-vehicle-adventures-with-google-maps/\">says it will use AI</a> to summarize customer reviews of EV chargers to display more specific directions to certain chargers, such as those located in parking garages or more hard-to-find places. And there will be more prompts in the app to encourage users to submit their feedback after using an EV charger \u2014 which wil", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132254/google-maps-ev-charging-directions-ai-summaries", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google Maps will use AI to help you find out-of-the-way EV chargers", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-17T09:58:41+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Take-Two Interactive logo against a white background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4HY7hLlSQ6tgxXvB9ozK_paG93s=/0x10:1920x1290/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73284358/Take_Two_interactive.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The company expects to complete its downsizing efforts by the end of this year.</em> | Image: Take-Two Interactive</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OfeMDk\">Take-Two Interactive, the gaming company behind franchises like <em>Grand Theft Auto</em>, <em>NBA 2K</em>, and <em>Bioshock</em>, has announced cost-cutting measures that will lay off \u201capproximately five percent\u201d of its global workforce and scrap several projects already in development.</p>\n<p id=\"AZKgjF\">The company said in an SEC filing <a href=\"https://taketwointeractivesoftwareinc.gcs-web.com/static-files/b6e34920-92be-4751-8b7a-7334558bf5ac\">published on Tuesday</a> that it is \u201cstreamlining its organizational structure, which will eliminate headc", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132791/taketwo-interactive-grand-theft-auto-layoffs-cut-projects", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_ra